blogs.title: Why Start a Fundraiser to Plant Trees?
blogs.content:
Our Reforestation Program plants millions of trees, reforesting thousands of acres of National Forests. Every tree planted can create lasting impacts that support climate change mitigation, and it’s always easier to tackle big challenges when you work together towards a common goal! That’s why the National Forest Foundation makes it easy to organize tree planting fundraisers where every dollar raised goes towards planting trees.

People start tree planting fundraisers for all sorts of reasons and with all sorts of crews. Watch our Instagram video for a step-by-step guide for how to get started and keep reading for a sampling of the types of fundraising teams that are helping us replant National Forests.
The holidays aren’t the only time of year to give back, especially on behalf of a loved one. It’s always the right time to give your best friend, partner, or cherished relative the gift of planting trees in their honor. One of the best ways to plant trees on behalf of a loved one, say on their birthday, your anniversary, or in their memory, is to bring everyone together who loves them and restore National Forests together.



There are so many different reasons and occasions to start a tree planting fundraiser. To learn how to get started, check out our Reforestation Fundraisers page. If you want to hear from the Reforestation Program crew for more information, watch our 4 tips for a successful fundraiser video. We need to band together and fundraise for reforestation!

Header photo by Dave Gardner Creative.

blogs.title: What Is The Best Value Option For High-Purity Water Systems?
blogs.content:
Los Angeles-based MECO was founded in 1928 as a small pump distributor. Nearly 100 years later, it has grown into the world leader in the engineering and manufacturing of water purification solutions, with locations in California, Texas, Puerto Rico, Chile, South Korea, Ireland, Spain, West Africa, China and Singapore.

Every one of its high-purity water systems strictly adheres to current Good Manufacturing Practices (cGMP). It follows the American Society of Mechanical Engineers’ design standards and is ISO 9001:2015 certified, demonstrating its commitment to consistent quality. It also verifies equipment performance through factory acceptance test (FAT) protocols. In short, these systems consistently surpass global standards.

With state-of-the-art facilities over 100,000 square feet, MECO can easily serve the food and beverage, biopharmaceutical, industrial, and desalination markets. Its advanced technologies and environmentally friendly practices make it a sound choice. You have numerous turnkey and customized options for ultrapure water production, whether you prefer steam sanitization, reverse osmosis (RO) or ultraviolet (UV) light.

Specialists custom-engineer every unit, ensuring they are built to last for your location and needs. Since each is wired, piped and assembled at the factory, your installation costs and startup time are minimal. The efficient layout simplifies calibration and maintenance, reducing operational, service and capital expenses.
Over two decades ago, Patty, Mark and Steve Timmons started US Water Systems in their garage. This family-owned and operated business has grown substantially since then, having served more than 100,000 customers. Its U.S.-based technicians also have over 300 years of combined technical expertise.

Whether you purchase high-purity, RO or deionization equipment, commercial options are available that can produce Type I, Type II, Type III or Type IV water. They range from 5 gallons per day to 16,000 pounds per day, so they will work regardless of your production rate. The skilled engineers will work with you to design a solution that meets your needs.

Your relationship with US Water Systems does not end once you receive your delivery. Unlike others, it covers post-sale support for your equipment’s entire lifespan. If you experience performance troubles within the first year of ownership, you can get a refund or replacement thanks to the 100% money-back guarantee. The products may not be the most affordable, but they offer excellent value.

This provider can sell directly to you because its plants and team are U.S.-based. Also, its salespeople do not earn commissions, which saves you up to 70% on the initial purchase compared to other entities. It uses industry-standard filters and membranes so you do not have to purchase expensive proprietary replacements, keeping thousands in your pocket over the life of your system. It even ships items for free for orders over $199.

blogs.title: Understanding Your Genetic Blueprint For A Healthier Life
blogs.content:
Your body needs the right mix of vitamins to stay strong and healthy. Some people get enough from food, but others may need more help. Your genes can show how well your body absorbs certain vitamins.

For example, you may have a hard time getting enough vitamin D, even if you spend time in the sun. Or your body might not use B vitamins as well as others. A DNA test can help find these issues early.

Once you know which vitamins your body needs more of, you can eat foods that support those needs. You can also choose the best supplements, if needed. This can help you feel better and avoid health problems later.

Balancing your vitamin levels can give you more energy and improve your focus. It also helps your immune system work better. Knowing your vitamin needs makes healthy eating easier.
Not every diet works the same for everyone. Your genes can tell you which foods your body handles well and which ones cause problems. A premium DNA kit for diet & fitness can help you learn all this.

Some people lose weight better with low-fat diets. Others do better with more protein or fewer carbs. Your DNA can guide you to the best plan for your body.

The test results can also show how your body reacts to sugar, fat, or salt. This makes it easier to cut out what harms you and eat more of what helps.

Choosing the right diet based on your genes can improve your health faster. You may have more energy, better digestion, and even sleep better. A diet that fits your body is easier to stick with long-term.
